  "insights": [
    "Revenue grew 18% YoY driven primarily by expansion into enterprise accounts, with enterprise ARPA up significantly due to bundled contracts.",
    "A pricing-tier simplification that raised mid-market costs coincided with churn rising from 3.1% to 4.0%, alongside higher downgrade/cancellation rates among smaller customers and slightly negative mid-tier sentiment.",
    "Support tickets increased 25%, mostly tied to billing confusion and feature access restrictions, suggesting the pricing/packaging change created friction; marketing spend also rose 15% during the period."
  ],
  "risk": "Mid-market and SMB retention risk is increasing due to pricing/packaging friction (billing confusion and perceived feature restrictions), potentially eroding growth gains from enterprise expansion and increasing support costs.",
  "next_action": "Run an urgent pricing/packaging and billing-UX remediation: analyze churn/tickets by cohort and plan, clarify invoices and feature entitlements, introduce a mid-market-friendly option (grandfathering/credits or adjusted tier), and monitor churn, downgrade rate, and ticket volume weekly."
